You are building "FitCore" — a Gym Management SaaS platform.

## UNIFIED PLATFORM ARCHITECTURE (RBAC)

### App 1: FitCore Mobile (Flutter) — Single app for all mobile users
Roles handled inside the same Flutter app:
  - MEMBER   → Home, Workouts, Diet, Attendance, Profile
  - TRAINER  → Dashboard, My Members, Create Plans, Schedule, Profile
  - RECEPTIONIST → Check-in, Member Lookup, Attendance Log, Profile

### App 2: FitCore Web Dashboard (React/Next.js) — Single web app for all admin users
Roles handled inside the same Next.js app:
  - GYM_OWNER    → Full gym management (members, trainers, plans, payments, reports)
  - SUPER_ADMIN  → SaaS management (all gyms, billing, platform analytics)
  - RECEPTIONIST → Limited web access (attendance, member lookup only)

## RBAC CORE RULES
- Role is returned in the JWT token payload: { userId, role, gymId, permissions[] }
- On app launch (after login), role is read from token → routing decision made
- Each screen/page checks role before rendering — unauthorized = redirect
- Navigation items, action buttons, and data views are filtered by role
- Permissions array allows fine-grained control within a role

## ROLE → ROUTE MAP

### Mobile (Flutter)
- MEMBER      → /member/* routes, BottomNav: Home | Workouts | Diet | Attendance | Profile
- TRAINER     → /trainer/* routes, BottomNav: Dashboard | Members | Plans | Schedule | Profile
- RECEPTIONIST→ /receptionist/* routes, BottomNav: Check-in | Members | Log | Profile

### Web (Next.js)
- GYM_OWNER   → /owner/* (full sidebar)
- SUPER_ADMIN → /superadmin/* (platform sidebar)
- RECEPTIONIST→ /receptionist/* (minimal sidebar)

## RBAC SERVICE (Flutter — lib/services/auth_service.dart)
- AuthService stores: UserModel { id, name, role, gymId, token, permissions }
- RoleGuard widget: wraps any widget, shows empty/redirect if role not allowed
- NavigationRouter: reads role from AuthService, returns correct shell + routes

## RBAC SERVICE (Web — lib/auth/rbac.ts)
- useAuth() hook returns: { user, role, permissions, hasPermission(key) }
- <PermissionGate permission="members:write"> component wraps guarded UI
- Middleware: reads JWT, redirects to correct dashboard path by role

## TECH STACK
- Mobile: Flutter (Dart) — single APK/IPA, role-based routing
- Web: React + Next.js 14 (App Router) + TailwindCSS
- Backend: Node.js + Express (mocked for prototype phase)
- Database: PostgreSQL (multi-tenant via gym_id)
- Auth: JWT with role + permissions in payload
- Payments: Razorpay
- Notifications: Firebase Push + WhatsApp + SMS
- State Management (Flutter): Riverpod

